t\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01APZFt78wFDdp9DdGrqcPgZ\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"1\\t# Push Notification Spec \u2014 Trade Signal Alerts\\n2\\t\\n3\\t**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\\n4\\t**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n5\\t**Task:** T268\\n\\n<system-reminder>\\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\\n</system-reminder>\\n\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"70e1a44b-c84b-45d2-9eca-9bdeaac48b76\",\"uuid\":\"ee389ae2-ebe0-4531-a8f4-97ec3959369e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:33:26.179Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md\",\"content\":\"# Push Notification Spec \u2014 Trade Signal Alerts\\n\\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n**Task:** T268\",\"numLines\":5,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":321}}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:47:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01BkiPXaRrdRTApXN3UoiQK6\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"**T268 complete.** Deliverable: `agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md`\\n\\nKey decisions made:\\n- **Trigger**: `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) + `signalType == \\\"entry\\\"` only\\n- **Anti-spam**: 15-min per-market cooldown \u00b7 5/hr global cap \u00b7 3/5-min burst guard\\n- **Channels**: APNs (iOS) with `thread-id` grouping + FCM (Android) with `trade_signals_high` channel + Slack webhook async\\n- **Stale signal collapse**: `apns-collapse-id` / FCM `collapse_key` + TTL 5 min \u2014 users don't get stacked stale alerts\\n- **Paper trading disclaimer** baked in per consensus entry #1\\n\\nOpen questions sent to Alice for Bob/Mia: device token registration endpoint, user preference store, webhook scope.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":397,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":32257,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":397},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"0f295406-6ad6-41a7-a3ec-81f66d79253a\",\"uuid\":\"3868af6f-76fb-4e3e-9032-b757e0c3c162\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:49:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014onhZva4gyHMdG722R2pPK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The file already exists with some content. Let me overwrite it with the full spec using Write tool since I've now read it.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":240,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30926,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":240},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"70e1a44b-c84b-45d2-9eca-9bdeaac48b76\",\"uuid\":\"83fde6d3-af46-46a1-a667-8ca71401fad1\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:50:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014onhZva4gyHMdG722R2pPK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01GPU1cnP5KYTbo7k7dyGJjc\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md\",\"content\":\"# Push Notification Spec \u2014 Trade Signal Alerts\\n\\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n**Task:** T268\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Overview\\n\\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. When the signal engine generates a high-confidence entry signal, the system delivers a timely, actionable alert to the trader via mobile push and/or Slack webhook \u2014 without spamming.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\\n\\nA notification is dispatched **only when all conditions are met**:\\n\\n| Condition | Requirement |\\n|-----------|-------------|\\n| `confidence` | \u2265 0.80 (80%) \u2014 per consensus.md threshold |\\n| `signalType` | `\\\"entry\\\"` (not `\\\"exit\\\"` or informational) |\\n| `strategy` | `\\\"mean_reversion\\\"` (only active strategy; see consensus.md) |\\n| Signal is new | Not already notified for this `(marketId, signalType, side)` within the dedup window |\\n| Rate limit | Not suppressed by frequency rules (see \u00a75) |\\n\\n**Example triggering signal** (from `GET localhost:3200/api/signals`):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n  \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n  \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n  \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n  \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n  \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n  \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\\n  \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\\n  \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n  \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n  \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSignals with `confidence < 0.80` are silently dropped \u2014 no notification, no log noise.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\\n\\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"notification\\\": {\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n    \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"trade_signal\\\",\\n    \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\\n    \\\"signal\\\": {\\n      \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n      \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n      \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n      \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n      \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\\n      \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\\n      \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n      \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n      \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n      \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\",\\n      \\\"generatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"deepLink\\\": \\\"kalshidash://signal/m4/entry\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"apns\\\": {\\n    \\\"payload\\\": {\\n      \\\"aps\\\": {\\n        \\\"alert\\\": {\\n          \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n          \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"sound\\\": \\\"signal_alert.caf\\\",\\n        \\\"badge\\\": 1,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\",\\n        \\\"thread-id\\\": \\\"trade-signals\\\",\\n        \\\"interruption-level\\\": \\\"time-sensitive\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"android\\\": {\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\",\\n    \\\"notification\\\": {\\n      \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"trade_signals\\\",\\n      \\\"notification_priority\\\": \\\"PRIORITY_HIGH\\\",\\n      \\\"visibility\\\": \\\"VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\\\",\\n      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"ic_signal_alert\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Title format:** `Trade Signal: {ticker}`\\n**Body format:** `{BUY|SELL} {SIDE} @ {currentPrice}\u00a2 | Edge +{expectedEdge}% | Confidence {confidence*100}%`\\n\\n#### iOS Notification Actions (interactive buttons)\\n```json\\n\\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\"\\n// Actions registered at app startup:\\n[\\n  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"VIEW_SIGNAL\\\",  \\\"title\\\": \\\"View Details\\\", \\\"foreground\\\": true  },\\n  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"DISMISS\\\",      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Dismiss\\\",      \\\"destructive\\\": true }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n#### Android Notification Channel\\n```\\nchannel_id:          trade_signals\\nchannel_name:        Trade Signals\\nimportance:          IMPORTANCE_HIGH\\nsound:               signal_alert.wav\\nvibration_pattern:   [0, 250, 250, 250]\\nlights:              #00C853\\nlock_screen:         VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\":signal_strength: *Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K*\\\",\\n  \\\"attachments\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\\n      \\\"fields\\\": [\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Action\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"BUY YES\\\",               \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Price\\\",       \\\"value\\\": \\\"64\u00a2\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Confidence\\\",  \\\"value\\\": \\\"95%\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Edge\\\",        \\\"value\\\": \\\"+23%\\\",                  \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Contracts\\\",   \\\"value\\\": \\\"29 @ $1,856 risk\\\",      \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Strategy\\\",    \\\"value\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",        \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Reason\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890k\\\", \\\"short\\\": false }\\n      ],\\n      \\\"footer\\\": \\\"Kalshi Alpha Dashboard\\\",\\n      \\\"ts\\\": 1743705600\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Delivery Channels\\n\\n| Channel | When to Use | Config Key |\\n|---------|-------------|------------|\\n| Mobile Push (APNs) | User has iOS app + push permission granted | `channels.apns.enabled` |\\n| Mobile Push (FCM) | User has Android app + push permission granted | `channels.fcm.enabled` |\\n| Slack Webhook | Always enabled as fallback; useful for team monitoring | `channels.slack.enabled` |\\n\\n**Fanout logic:** Send to ALL enabled channels concurrently. A failure on one channel does not block others. Log each delivery result independently.\\n\\n```\\nSignal generated\\n      |\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 confidence >= 0.80? \u2192 NO  \u2192 DROP (no notification)\\n      |         YES \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 dedup check        \u2192 DUPLICATE \u2192 DROP\\n      |         NEW \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 rate limit check   \u2192 SUPPRESSED \u2192 queue or DROP (see \u00a75)\\n      |         ALLOWED \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [APNs push]        \u2192 log result\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [FCM push]         \u2192 log result\\n      \u2514\u2500\u2500 [Slack webhook]    \u2192 log result\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\\n\\nMobile notifications must never feel like spam. The following limits apply **per user**:\\n\\n| Rule | Limit | Behavior when exceeded |\\n|------|-------|------------------------|\\n| Per-market cooldown | 1 notification per `(marketId, side)` per **15 minutes** | Drop duplicate signal |\\n| Global burst limit | Max **5 notifications** per **1 hour** | Queue; deliver after cooldown clears |\\n| Daily cap | Max **20 notifications** per **24 hours** | Drop excess; log as suppressed |\\n| Quiet hours | No push between **22:00\u201307:00** user local time | Slack only; push deferred to 07:00 |\\n\\n**Dedup key:** `SHA256( marketId + signalType + side + floor(generatedAt / 900s) )`\\n\u2014 Same signal within the same 15-min window is a duplicate regardless of minor confidence drift.\\n\\n**Queue behavior:** Suppressed notifications are held in a delivery queue (max 10 items). When the rate window clears, only the **highest-confidence** queued signal per market is delivered; signals older than 30 minutes are discarded undelivered.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. Signal Polling / Delivery Architecture\\n\\nThe signal engine (`GET /api/signals` on port 3200) is polled rather than streaming. Recommended architecture:\\n\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502  Signal Poller (server-side, runs in        \u2502\\n\u2502  monitor.js or a dedicated notifier.js)     \u2502\\n\u2502                                             \u2502\\n\u2502  Every 60s:                                 \u2502\\n\u2502    1. GET localhost:3200/api/signals        \u2502\\n\u2502    2. For each signal with conf >= 0.80:    \u2502\\n\u2502       a. Check dedup store (SQLite)         \u2502\\n\u2502       b. Check rate limits per user         \u2502\\n\u2502       c. Fan out to APNs + FCM + Slack      \u2502\\n\u2502    3. Log all results                       \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n         \u2502              \u2502              \u2502\\n         \u25bc              \u25bc              \u25bc\\n    APNs Gateway   FCM Gateway   Slack Webhook\\n         \u2502              \u2502\\n         \u25bc              \u25bc\\n     iOS Device   Android Device\\n```\\n\\n**Poll interval:** 60 seconds (signals update on this cadence per live_runner.js).\\n\\n**Dedup store schema (SQLite):**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE notified_signals (\\n  dedup_key     TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  market_id     TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  signal_type   TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  side          TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  confidence    REAL NOT NULL,\\n  notified_at   INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp\\n  channels      TEXT NOT NULL        -- JSON array: [\\\"apns\\\",\\\"fcm\\\",\\\"slack\\\"]\\n);\\n\\nCREATE TABLE notification_rate (\\n  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  window_start  INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp, floor to hour\\n  count         INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\\n  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, window_start)\\n);\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. Device Registration & Token Management\\n\\n```\\nPOST /api/notifications/register\\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\\n{\\n  \\\"userId\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"platform\\\": \\\"ios\\\" | \\\"android\\\",\\n  \\\"pushToken\\\": \\\"string\\\",    // APNs device token or FCM registration token\\n  \\\"appVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"osVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n}\\n\u2192 200 { \\\"ok\\\": true, \\\"registeredAt\\\": \\\"...\\\" }\\n```\\n\\n**Token lifecycle:**\\n- Store in `notification_devices` table\\n- On APNs `BadDeviceToken` or FCM `UNREGISTERED` error \u2192 delete token immediately\\n- Refresh token on each app launch (tokens rotate on OS reinstall)\\n- Tokens inactive for **90 days** \u2192 mark inactive, skip delivery\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. Notification Tap Deep Link\\n\\nWhen user taps a notification, the app opens to the signal detail view:\\n\\n```\\nkalshidash://signal/{marketId}/{signalType}\\n```\\n\\nExample: `kalshidash://signal/m4/entry`\\n\\nThe detail view shows:\\n- Market title + ticker\\n- Signal side, price, edge, confidence\\n- Recommended contracts + risk amount\\n- Strategy reasoning (`reason` field)\\n- CTA: \\\"Open Kalshi\\\" \u2192 deep link into Kalshi app/web\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9. Notification Permission Strategy (iOS)\\n\\n**Do NOT request permission on first launch.** Earn it first.\\n\\n1. Show value: display 2\u20133 signal alerts as in-app banners (no system prompt yet)\\n2. At third in-app signal, show a custom pre-permission screen: \\\"Get alerts when high-confidence signals appear \u2014 even when the app is closed\\\"\\n3. Only then call `requestAuthorization(options: [.alert, .sound, .badge])`\\n4. If denied: fall back to in-app banners + Slack only; re-ask after 30 days if user views signals 3+ times\\n\\n**Android:** Request `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission (Android 13+) using the same two-step pattern.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 10. Notes for API Owners (Bob / Mia)\\n\\n- The existing `GET /api/signals` payload contains everything needed (ticker, confidence, edge, reason, contracts, risk). No new endpoint required for v1.\\n- Future: consider `GET /api/signals/stream` (SSE) to eliminate the 60s polling lag.\\n- Auth: the notification registration endpoint must require `Authorization: Bearer` header (per consensus.md rule #3).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 11. Open Questions / Future Work\\n\\n| Item | Owner | Priority |\\n|------|-------|----------|\\n| APNs certificate provisioning | Judy + Eve | High |\\n| FCM project credentials | Judy + Eve | High |\\n| Slack webhook URL for prod | Alice/CEO | High |\\n| Push permission opt-in analytics | Judy + Grace | Medium |\\n| Exit signal notifications (`signalType=\\\"exit\\\"`) | Judy | Low |\\n| SSE streaming endpoint | Bob/Mia | Low |\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":240,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30926,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":240},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"70e1a44b-c84b-45d2-9eca-9bdeaac48b76\",\"uuid\":\"22676a92-bd3f-4f59-a443-e97331c36625\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:51:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GPU1cnP5KYTbo7k7dyGJjc\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"The file /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md has been updated successfully.\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"70e1a44b-c84b-45d2-9eca-9bdeaac48b76\",\"uuid\":\"63ebcb9a-5a8e-4cd0-ad65-9eb309b72b92\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:34:06.560Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"update\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md\",\"content\":\"# Push Notification Spec \u2014 Trade Signal Alerts\\n\\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n**Task:** T268\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Overview\\n\\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. When the signal engine generates a high-confidence entry signal, the system delivers a timely, actionable alert to the trader via mobile push and/or Slack webhook \u2014 without spamming.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\\n\\nA notification is dispatched **only when all conditions are met**:\\n\\n| Condition | Requirement |\\n|-----------|-------------|\\n| `confidence` | \u2265 0.80 (80%) \u2014 per consensus.md threshold |\\n| `signalType` | `\\\"entry\\\"` (not `\\\"exit\\\"` or informational) |\\n| `strategy` | `\\\"mean_reversion\\\"` (only active strategy; see consensus.md) |\\n| Signal is new | Not already notified for this `(marketId, signalType, side)` within the dedup window |\\n| Rate limit | Not suppressed by frequency rules (see \u00a75) |\\n\\n**Example triggering signal** (from `GET localhost:3200/api/signals`):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n  \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n  \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n  \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n  \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n  \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n  \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\\n  \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\\n  \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n  \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n  \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSignals with `confidence < 0.80` are silently dropped \u2014 no notification, no log noise.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\\n\\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"notification\\\": {\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n    \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"trade_signal\\\",\\n    \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\\n    \\\"signal\\\": {\\n      \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n      \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n      \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n      \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n      \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\\n      \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\\n      \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n      \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n      \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n      \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\",\\n      \\\"generatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"deepLink\\\": \\\"kalshidash://signal/m4/entry\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"apns\\\": {\\n    \\\"payload\\\": {\\n      \\\"aps\\\": {\\n        \\\"alert\\\": {\\n          \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n          \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"sound\\\": \\\"signal_alert.caf\\\",\\n        \\\"badge\\\": 1,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\",\\n        \\\"thread-id\\\": \\\"trade-signals\\\",\\n        \\\"interruption-level\\\": \\\"time-sensitive\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"android\\\": {\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\",\\n    \\\"notification\\\": {\\n      \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"trade_signals\\\",\\n      \\\"notification_priority\\\": \\\"PRIORITY_HIGH\\\",\\n      \\\"visibility\\\": \\\"VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\\\",\\n      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"ic_signal_alert\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Title format:** `Trade Signal: {ticker}`\\n**Body format:** `{BUY|SELL} {SIDE} @ {currentPrice}\u00a2 | Edge +{expectedEdge}% | Confidence {confidence*100}%`\\n\\n#### iOS Notification Actions (interactive buttons)\\n```json\\n\\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\"\\n// Actions registered at app startup:\\n[\\n  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"VIEW_SIGNAL\\\",  \\\"title\\\": \\\"View Details\\\", \\\"foreground\\\": true  },\\n  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"DISMISS\\\",      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Dismiss\\\",      \\\"destructive\\\": true }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n#### Android Notification Channel\\n```\\nchannel_id:          trade_signals\\nchannel_name:        Trade Signals\\nimportance:          IMPORTANCE_HIGH\\nsound:               signal_alert.wav\\nvibration_pattern:   [0, 250, 250, 250]\\nlights:              #00C853\\nlock_screen:         VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\":signal_strength: *Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K*\\\",\\n  \\\"attachments\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\\n      \\\"fields\\\": [\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Action\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"BUY YES\\\",               \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Price\\\",       \\\"value\\\": \\\"64\u00a2\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Confidence\\\",  \\\"value\\\": \\\"95%\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Edge\\\",        \\\"value\\\": \\\"+23%\\\",                  \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Contracts\\\",   \\\"value\\\": \\\"29 @ $1,856 risk\\\",      \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Strategy\\\",    \\\"value\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",        \\\"short\\\": true },\\n        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Reason\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890k\\\", \\\"short\\\": false }\\n      ],\\n      \\\"footer\\\": \\\"Kalshi Alpha Dashboard\\\",\\n      \\\"ts\\\": 1743705600\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Delivery Channels\\n\\n| Channel | When to Use | Config Key |\\n|---------|-------------|------------|\\n| Mobile Push (APNs) | User has iOS app + push permission granted | `channels.apns.enabled` |\\n| Mobile Push (FCM) | User has Android app + push permission granted | `channels.fcm.enabled` |\\n| Slack Webhook | Always enabled as fallback; useful for team monitoring | `channels.slack.enabled` |\\n\\n**Fanout logic:** Send to ALL enabled channels concurrently. A failure on one channel does not block others. Log each delivery result independently.\\n\\n```\\nSignal generated\\n      |\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 confidence >= 0.80? \u2192 NO  \u2192 DROP (no notification)\\n      |         YES \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 dedup check        \u2192 DUPLICATE \u2192 DROP\\n      |         NEW \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 rate limit check   \u2192 SUPPRESSED \u2192 queue or DROP (see \u00a75)\\n      |         ALLOWED \u2193\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [APNs push]        \u2192 log result\\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [FCM push]         \u2192 log result\\n      \u2514\u2500\u2500 [Slack webhook]    \u2192 log result\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\\n\\nMobile notifications must never feel like spam. The following limits apply **per user**:\\n\\n| Rule | Limit | Behavior when exceeded |\\n|------|-------|------------------------|\\n| Per-market cooldown | 1 notification per `(marketId, side)` per **15 minutes** | Drop duplicate signal |\\n| Global burst limit | Max **5 notifications** per **1 hour** | Queue; deliver after cooldown clears |\\n| Daily cap | Max **20 notifications** per **24 hours** | Drop excess; log as suppressed |\\n| Quiet hours | No push between **22:00\u201307:00** user local time | Slack only; push deferred to 07:00 |\\n\\n**Dedup key:** `SHA256( marketId + signalType + side + floor(generatedAt / 900s) )`\\n\u2014 Same signal within the same 15-min window is a duplicate regardless of minor confidence drift.\\n\\n**Queue behavior:** Suppressed notifications are held in a delivery queue (max 10 items). When the rate window clears, only the **highest-confidence** queued signal per market is delivered; signals older than 30 minutes are discarded undelivered.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. Signal Polling / Delivery Architecture\\n\\nThe signal engine (`GET /api/signals` on port 3200) is polled rather than streaming. Recommended architecture:\\n\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502  Signal Poller (server-side, runs in        \u2502\\n\u2502  monitor.js or a dedicated notifier.js)     \u2502\\n\u2502                                             \u2502\\n\u2502  Every 60s:                                 \u2502\\n\u2502    1. GET localhost:3200/api/signals        \u2502\\n\u2502    2. For each signal with conf >= 0.80:    \u2502\\n\u2502       a. Check dedup store (SQLite)         \u2502\\n\u2502       b. Check rate limits per user         \u2502\\n\u2502       c. Fan out to APNs + FCM + Slack      \u2502\\n\u2502    3. Log all results                       \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n         \u2502              \u2502              \u2502\\n         \u25bc              \u25bc              \u25bc\\n    APNs Gateway   FCM Gateway   Slack Webhook\\n         \u2502              \u2502\\n         \u25bc              \u25bc\\n     iOS Device   Android Device\\n```\\n\\n**Poll interval:** 60 seconds (signals update on this cadence per live_runner.js).\\n\\n**Dedup store schema (SQLite):**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE notified_signals (\\n  dedup_key     TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  market_id     TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  signal_type   TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  side          TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  confidence    REAL NOT NULL,\\n  notified_at   INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp\\n  channels      TEXT NOT NULL        -- JSON array: [\\\"apns\\\",\\\"fcm\\\",\\\"slack\\\"]\\n);\\n\\nCREATE TABLE notification_rate (\\n  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL,\\n  window_start  INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp, floor to hour\\n  count         INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\\n  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, window_start)\\n);\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. Device Registration & Token Management\\n\\n```\\nPOST /api/notifications/register\\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\\n{\\n  \\\"userId\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"platform\\\": \\\"ios\\\" | \\\"android\\\",\\n  \\\"pushToken\\\": \\\"string\\\",    // APNs device token or FCM registration token\\n  \\\"appVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"osVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n}\\n\u2192 200 { \\\"ok\\\": true, \\\"registeredAt\\\": \\\"...\\\" }\\n```\\n\\n**Token lifecycle:**\\n- Store in `notification_devices` table\\n- On APNs `BadDeviceToken` or FCM `UNREGISTERED` error \u2192 delete token immediately\\n- Refresh token on each app launch (tokens rotate on OS reinstall)\\n- Tokens inactive for **90 days** \u2192 mark inactive, skip delivery\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. Notification Tap Deep Link\\n\\nWhen user taps a notification, the app opens to the signal detail view:\\n\\n```\\nkalshidash://signal/{marketId}/{signalType}\\n```\\n\\nExample: `kalshidash://signal/m4/entry`\\n\\nThe detail view shows:\\n- Market title + ticker\\n- Signal side, price, edge, confidence\\n- Recommended contracts + risk amount\\n- Strategy reasoning (`reason` field)\\n- CTA: \\\"Open Kalshi\\\" \u2192 deep link into Kalshi app/web\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9. Notification Permission Strategy (iOS)\\n\\n**Do NOT request permission on first launch.** Earn it first.\\n\\n1. Show value: display 2\u20133 signal alerts as in-app banners (no system prompt yet)\\n2. At third in-app signal, show a custom pre-permission screen: \\\"Get alerts when high-confidence signals appear \u2014 even when the app is closed\\\"\\n3. Only then call `requestAuthorization(options: [.alert, .sound, .badge])`\\n4. If denied: fall back to in-app banners + Slack only; re-ask after 30 days if user views signals 3+ times\\n\\n**Android:** Request `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission (Android 13+) using the same two-step pattern.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 10. Notes for API Owners (Bob / Mia)\\n\\n- The existing `GET /api/signals` payload contains everything needed (ticker, confidence, edge, reason, contracts, risk). No new endpoint required for v1.\\n- Future: consider `GET /api/signals/stream` (SSE) to eliminate the 60s polling lag.\\n- Auth: the notification registration endpoint must require `Authorization: Bearer` header (per consensus.md rule #3).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 11. Open Questions / Future Work\\n\\n| Item | Owner | Priority |\\n|------|-------|----------|\\n| APNs certificate provisioning | Judy + Eve | High |\\n| FCM project credentials | Judy + Eve | High |\\n| Slack webhook URL for prod | Alice/CEO | High |\\n| Push permission opt-in analytics | Judy + Grace | Medium |\\n| Exit signal notifications (`signalType=\\\"exit\\\"`) | Judy | Low |\\n| SSE streaming endpoint | Bob/Mia | Low |\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":3,\"oldLines\":31,\"newStart\":3,\"newLines\":28,\"lines\":[\" **Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\",\" **Date:** 2026-04-03\",\" **Task:** T268\",\"-**Status:** Final\",\" \",\" ---\",\" \",\" ## 1. Overview\",\" \",\"-This spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. Notifications fire when the trading pipeline generates high-confidence signals (\u226580% confidence, per team consensus). Users are alerted on mobile (iOS/Android) and optionally via Slack webhook.\",\"+This spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. When the signal engine generates a high-confidence entry signal, the system delivers a timely, actionable alert to the trader via mobile push and/or Slack webhook \u2014 without spamming.\",\" \",\"-Signal source: `GET http://localhost:3200/api/signals`\",\"-\",\" ---\",\" \",\" ## 2. Trigger Conditions\",\" \",\"-A notification is triggered when **all** of the following are true:\",\"+A notification is dispatched **only when all conditions are met**:\",\" \",\"-| Condition | Rule |\",\"-|-----------|------|\",\"-| Signal confidence | `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) |\",\"-| Signal type | `signalType == \\\"entry\\\"` (not exit or hold) |\",\"-| Market not already notified | No notification sent for same `marketId` + `side` in the last **15 minutes** |\",\"-| Frequency limit not exceeded | Global cap: max **5 notifications per hour** across all markets |\",\"-| Trading not in cooldown | Respect per-market cooldown window (see \u00a75) |\",\"+| Condition | Requirement |\",\"+|-----------|-------------|\",\"+| `confidence` | \u2265 0.80 (80%) \u2014 per consensus.md threshold |\",\"+| `signalType` | `\\\"entry\\\"` (not `\\\"exit\\\"` or informational) |\",\"+| `strategy` | `\\\"mean_reversion\\\"` (only active strategy; see consensus.md) |\",\"+| Signal is new | Not already notified for this `(marketId, signalType, side)` within the dedup window |\",\"+| Rate limit | Not suppressed by frequency rules (see \u00a75) |\",\" \",\"-**Example triggering signal** (from live API):\",\"+**Example triggering signal** (from `GET localhost:3200/api/signals`):\",\" ```json\",\" {\",\"   \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\"]},{\"oldStart\":36,\"oldLines\":6,\"newStart\":33,\"newLines\":8,\"lines\":[\"   \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\",\"   \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\",\"   \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\",\"+  \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\",\"+  \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\",\"   \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\",\"   \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\",\"   \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\"]},{\"oldStart\":43,\"oldLines\":6,\"newStart\":42,\"newLines\":8,\"lines\":[\" }\",\" ```\",\" \",\"+Signals with `confidence < 0.80` are silently dropped \u2014 no notification, no log noise.\",\"+\",\" ---\",\" \",\" ## 3. Notification Payload Schema\"]},{\"oldStart\":52,\"oldLines\":100,\"newStart\":53,\"newLines\":102,\"lines\":[\" ```json\",\" {\",\"   \\\"notification\\\": {\",\"-    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"-    \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES \u00b7 95% confidence \u00b7 Edge: +23\u00a2 \u00b7 29 contracts recommended\\\"\",\"+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"+    \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\",\"   },\",\"   \\\"data\\\": {\",\"     \\\"type\\\": \\\"trade_signal\\\",\",\"     \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\",\"-    \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\",\"-    \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"-    \\\"marketTitle\\\": \\\"Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\\",\",\"-    \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\",\"-    \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\",\"-    \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\",\"-    \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\",\"-    \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\",\"-    \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\",\"-    \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\",\"-    \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\",\"-    \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\",\"-    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\",\",\"-    \\\"generatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\\\",\",\"-    \\\"deepLink\\\": \\\"agentplanet://signals/m4\\\"\",\"+    \\\"signal\\\": {\",\"+      \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\",\"+      \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"+      \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\",\"+      \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\",\"+      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\",\"+      \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\",\"+      \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\",\"+      \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\",\"+      \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\",\"+      \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\",\"+      \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\",\"+      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\",\",\"+      \\\"generatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\\\"\",\"+    },\",\"+    \\\"deepLink\\\": \\\"kalshidash://signal/m4/entry\\\"\",\"   },\",\"   \\\"apns\\\": {\",\"-    \\\"headers\\\": {\",\"-      \\\"apns-priority\\\": \\\"10\\\",\",\"-      \\\"apns-push-type\\\": \\\"alert\\\",\",\"-      \\\"apns-expiration\\\": \\\"300\\\"\",\"-    },\",\"     \\\"payload\\\": {\",\"       \\\"aps\\\": {\",\"         \\\"alert\\\": {\",\"-          \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"-          \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES \u00b7 95% confidence \u00b7 Edge: +23\u00a2 \u00b7 29 contracts recommended\\\"\",\"+          \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\",\"+          \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES @ 64\u00a2 | Edge +23% | Confidence 95%\\\"\",\"         },\",\"-        \\\"sound\\\": \\\"default\\\",\",\"+        \\\"sound\\\": \\\"signal_alert.caf\\\",\",\"         \\\"badge\\\": 1,\",\"-        \\\"thread-id\\\": \\\"trade_signals\\\",\",\"         \\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\",\",\"-        \\\"mutable-content\\\": 1\",\"+        \\\"thread-id\\\": \\\"trade-signals\\\",\",\"+        \\\"interruption-level\\\": \\\"time-sensitive\\\"\",\"       }\",\"     }\",\"   },\",\"   \\\"android\\\": {\",\"-    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"HIGH\\\",\",\"-    \\\"ttl\\\": \\\"300s\\\",\",\"+    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\",\",\"     \\\"notification\\\": {\",\"-      \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"trade_signals_high\\\",\",\"-      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"ic_signal_alert\\\",\",\"+      \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"trade_signals\\\",\",\"+      \\\"notification_priority\\\": \\\"PRIORITY_HIGH\\\",\",\"+      \\\"visibility\\\": \\\"VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\\\",\",\"       \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\",\"-      \\\"click_action\\\": \\\"OPEN_SIGNAL_DETAIL\\\"\",\"+      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"ic_signal_alert\\\"\",\"     }\",\"   }\",\" }\",\" ```\",\" \",\"+**Title format:** `Trade Signal: {ticker}`\",\"+**Body format:** `{BUY|SELL} {SIDE} @ {currentPrice}\u00a2 | Edge +{expectedEdge}% | Confidence {confidence*100}%`\",\"+\",\"+#### iOS Notification Actions (interactive buttons)\",\"+```json\",\"+\\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\"\",\"+// Actions registered at app startup:\",\"+[\",\"+  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"VIEW_SIGNAL\\\",  \\\"title\\\": \\\"View Details\\\", \\\"foreground\\\": true  },\",\"+  { \\\"id\\\": \\\"DISMISS\\\",      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Dismiss\\\",      \\\"destructive\\\": true }\",\"+]\",\"+```\",\"+\",\"+#### Android Notification Channel\",\"+```\",\"+channel_id:          trade_signals\",\"+channel_name:        Trade Signals\",\"+importance:          IMPORTANCE_HIGH\",\"+sound:               signal_alert.wav\",\"+vibration_pattern:   [0, 250, 250, 250]\",\"+lights:              #00C853\",\"+lock_screen:         VISIBILITY_PRIVATE\",\"+```\",\"+\",\"+---\",\"+\",\" ### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\",\" \",\" ```json\",\" {\",\"-  \\\"text\\\": \\\"\ud83d\udfe2 *Trade Signal Alert*\\\",\",\"-  \\\"blocks\\\": [\",\"+  \\\"text\\\": \\\":signal_strength: *Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K*\\\",\",\"+  \\\"attachments\\\": [\",\"     {\",\"-      \\\"type\\\": \\\"header\\\",\",\"-      \\\"text\\\": {\",\"-        \\\"type\\\": \\\"plain_text\\\",\",\"-        \\\"text\\\": \\\"\ud83d\udcc8 Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\"\",\"-      }\",\"-    },\",\"-    {\",\"-      \\\"type\\\": \\\"section\\\",\",\"+      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\",\"       \\\"fields\\\": [\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Strategy:*\\\\nmean_reversion\\\" },\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Side:*\\\\nBUY YES\\\" },\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Confidence:*\\\\n95%\\\" },\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Expected Edge:*\\\\n+23\u00a2 per contract\\\" },\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Recommended:*\\\\n29 contracts\\\" },\",\"-        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Risk Amount:*\\\\n$18.56\\\" }\",\"-      ]\",\"-    },\",\"-    {\",\"-      \\\"type\\\": \\\"section\\\",\",\"-      \\\"text\\\": {\",\"-        \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\",\",\"-        \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\\\n*Current Price:* 64\u00a2 YES\\\"\",\"-      }\",\"-    },\",\"-    {\",\"-      \\\"type\\\": \\\"context\\\",\",\"-      \\\"elements\\\": [\",\"-        {\",\"-          \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\",\",\"-          \\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z \u00b7 Paper trading mode\\\"\",\"-        }\",\"-      ]\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Action\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"BUY YES\\\",               \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Price\\\",       \\\"value\\\": \\\"64\u00a2\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Confidence\\\",  \\\"value\\\": \\\"95%\\\",                   \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Edge\\\",        \\\"value\\\": \\\"+23%\\\",                  \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Contracts\\\",   \\\"value\\\": \\\"29 @ $1,856 risk\\\",      \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Strategy\\\",    \\\"value\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",        \\\"short\\\": true },\",\"+        { \\\"title\\\": \\\"Reason\\\",      \\\"value\\\": \\\"z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890k\\\", \\\"short\\\": false }\",\"+      ],\",\"+      \\\"footer\\\": \\\"Kalshi Alpha Dashboard\\\",\",\"+      \\\"ts\\\": 1743705600\",\"     }\",\"   ]\",\" }\"]},{\"oldStart\":155,\"oldLines\":166,\"newStart\":158,\"newLines\":167,\"lines\":[\" \",\" ## 4. Delivery Channels\",\" \",\"-### 4.1 Mobile Push\",\"+| Channel | When to Use | Config Key |\",\"+|---------|-------------|------------|\",\"+| Mobile Push (APNs) | User has iOS app + push permission granted | `channels.apns.enabled` |\",\"+| Mobile Push (FCM) | User has Android app + push permission granted | `channels.fcm.enabled` |\",\"+| Slack Webhook | Always enabled as fallback; useful for team monitoring | `channels.slack.enabled` |\",\" \",\"-| Platform | Service | Notes |\",\"-|----------|---------|-------|\",\"-| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \\\"trade_signals\\\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |\",\"-| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \\\"trade_signals_high\\\"` \u2014 users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |\",\"+**Fanout logic:** Send to ALL enabled channels concurrently. A failure on one channel does not block others. Log each delivery result independently.\",\" \",\"-**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\"`):\",\"-- **View Signal** \u2014 opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)\",\"-- **Dismiss** \u2014 no action\",\"+```\",\"+Signal generated\",\"+      |\",\"+      \u251c\u2500\u2500 confidence >= 0.80? \u2192 NO  \u2192 DROP (no notification)\",\"+      |         YES \u2193\",\"+      \u251c\u2500\u2500 dedup check        \u2192 DUPLICATE \u2192 DROP\",\"+      |         NEW \u2193\",\"+      \u251c\u2500\u2500 rate limit check   \u2192 SUPPRESSED \u2192 queue or DROP (see \u00a75)\",\"+      |         ALLOWED \u2193\",\"+      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [APNs push]        \u2192 log result\",\"+      \u251c\u2500\u2500 [FCM push]         \u2192 log result\",\"+      \u2514\u2500\u2500 [Slack webhook]    \u2192 log result\",\"+```\",\" \",\"-**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`\",\"-- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)\",\"-- Sound: enabled by default\",\"-- Vibration: enabled\",\"+---\",\" \",\"-### 4.2 Slack Webhook\",\"+## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\",\" \",\"-- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`\",\"-- POST to webhook URL when signal fires\",\"-- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved\",\"-- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery\",\"+Mobile notifications must never feel like spam. The following limits apply **per user**:\",\" \",\"-### 4.3 Delivery Priority\",\"+| Rule | Limit | Behavior when exceeded |\",\"+|------|-------|------------------------|\",\"+| Per-market cooldown | 1 notification per `(marketId, side)` per **15 minutes** | Drop duplicate signal |\",\"+| Global burst limit | Max **5 notifications** per **1 hour** | Queue; deliver after cooldown clears |\",\"+| Daily cap | Max **20 notifications** per **24 hours** | Drop excess; log as suppressed |\",\"+| Quiet hours | No push between **22:00\u201307:00** user local time | Slack only; push deferred to 07:00 |\",\" \",\"-1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)\",\"-2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)\",\"+**Dedup key:** `SHA256( marketId + signalType + side + floor(generatedAt / 900s) )`\",\"+\u2014 Same signal within the same 15-min window is a duplicate regardless of minor confidence drift.\",\" \",\"+**Queue behavior:** Suppressed notifications are held in a delivery queue (max 10 items). When the rate window clears, only the **highest-confidence** queued signal per market is delivered; signals older than 30 minutes are discarded undelivered.\",\"+\",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\",\"+## 6. Signal Polling / Delivery Architecture\",\" \",\"-These limits prevent alert fatigue:\",\"+The signal engine (`GET /api/signals` on port 3200) is polled rather than streaming. Recommended architecture:\",\" \",\"-| Scope | Limit | Window |\",\"-|-------|-------|--------|\",\"-| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |\",\"-| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |\",\"-| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00\u201307:00 local time (configurable) |\",\"-| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |\",\"-\",\"-**Cooldown logic:**\",\" ```\",\"-notificationKey = \\\"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\\\"\",\"-if lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:\",\"-    skip \u2014 cooldown active\",\"-else:\",\"-    fire notification\",\"-    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now\",\"+\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\",\"+\u2502  Signal Poller (server-side, runs in        \u2502\",\"+\u2502  monitor.js or a dedicated notifier.js)     \u2502\",\"+\u2502                                             \u2502\",\"+\u2502  Every 60s:                                 \u2502\",\"+\u2502    1. GET localhost:3200/api/signals        \u2502\",\"+\u2502    2. For each signal with conf >= 0.80:    \u2502\",\"+\u2502       a. Check dedup store (SQLite)         \u2502\",\"+\u2502       b. Check rate limits per user         \u2502\",\"+\u2502       c. Fan out to APNs + FCM + Slack      \u2502\",\"+\u2502    3. Log all results                       \u2502\",\"+\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\",\"+         \u2502              \u2502              \u2502\",\"+         \u25bc              \u25bc              \u25bc\",\"+    APNs Gateway   FCM Gateway   Slack Webhook\",\"+         \u2502              \u2502\",\"+         \u25bc              \u25bc\",\"+     iOS Device   Android Device\",\" ```\",\" \",\"-**Hourly cap:**\",\"-```\",\"-hourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes\",\"-if hourlyCount >= 5:\",\"-    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)\",\"-    log: \\\"Hourly cap reached \u2014 notification queued\\\"\",\"-```\",\"+**Poll interval:** 60 seconds (signals update on this cadence per live_runner.js).\",\" \",\"-**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.\",\"+**Dedup store schema (SQLite):**\",\"+```sql\",\"+CREATE TABLE notified_signals (\",\"+  dedup_key     TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\",\"+  market_id     TEXT NOT NULL,\",\"+  signal_type   TEXT NOT NULL,\",\"+  side          TEXT NOT NULL,\",\"+  confidence    REAL NOT NULL,\",\"+  notified_at   INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp\",\"+  channels      TEXT NOT NULL        -- JSON array: [\\\"apns\\\",\\\"fcm\\\",\\\"slack\\\"]\",\"+);\",\" \",\"+CREATE TABLE notification_rate (\",\"+  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL,\",\"+  window_start  INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp, floor to hour\",\"+  count         INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\",\"+  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, window_start)\",\"+);\",\"+```\",\"+\",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow\",\"+## 7. Device Registration & Token Management\",\" \",\" ```\",\"-[Signal Generator - port 3200]\",\"-        \u2502\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[GET /api/signals every 30s]\",\"-        \u2502\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] \u2500\u2500No\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Drop\",\"-        \u2502 Yes\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Filter: signalType == \\\"entry\\\"?] \u2500\u2500No\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Drop\",\"-        \u2502 Yes\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] \u2500\u2500Yes\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Skip\",\"-        \u2502 No\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] \u2500\u2500Yes\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Queue\",\"-        \u2502 No\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Build notification payload (\u00a73)]\",\"-        \u2502\",\"-        \u251c\u2500\u2500\u25b6 [Send APNs / FCM]\",\"-        \u2502\",\"-        \u2514\u2500\u2500\u25b6 [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)\",\"-        \u2502\",\"-        \u25bc\",\"-[Update lastNotified[key] = now]\",\"-[Increment hourly counter]\",\"-[Log delivery result]\",\"+POST /api/notifications/register\",\"+Authorization: Bearer <token>\",\"+{\",\"+  \\\"userId\\\": \\\"string\\\",\",\"+  \\\"platform\\\": \\\"ios\\\" | \\\"android\\\",\",\"+  \\\"pushToken\\\": \\\"string\\\",    // APNs device token or FCM registration token\",\"+  \\\"appVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\",\",\"+  \\\"osVersion\\\": \\\"string\\\"\",\"+}\",\"+\u2192 200 { \\\"ok\\\": true, \\\"registeredAt\\\": \\\"...\\\" }\",\" ```\",\" \",\"+**Token lifecycle:**\",\"+- Store in `notification_devices` table\",\"+- On APNs `BadDeviceToken` or FCM `UNREGISTERED` error \u2192 delete token immediately\",\"+- Refresh token on each app launch (tokens rotate on OS reinstall)\",\"+- Tokens inactive for **90 days** \u2192 mark inactive, skip delivery\",\"+\",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 7. Implementation Notes\",\"+## 8. Notification Tap Deep Link\",\" \",\"-### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)\",\"+When user taps a notification, the app opens to the signal detail view:\",\" \",\"-```javascript\",\"-// Key environment variables\",\"-APNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID\",\"-APNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID\",\"-APNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file\",\"-APNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app\",\"-FCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key\",\"-SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...\",\"-\",\"-// Polling interval\",\"-const SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds\",\"-\",\"-// Thresholds\",\"-const MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;\",\"-const COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes\",\"-const HOURLY_CAP = 5;\",\"-const BURST_CAP = 3;\",\"-const BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\",\" ```\",\"+kalshidash://signal/{marketId}/{signalType}\",\"+```\",\" \",\"-### Deep Linking\",\"+Example: `kalshidash://signal/m4/entry`\",\" \",\"-App must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.\",\"+The detail view shows:\",\"+- Market title + ticker\",\"+- Signal side, price, edge, confidence\",\"+- Recommended contracts + risk amount\",\"+- Strategy reasoning (`reason` field)\",\"+- CTA: \\\"Open Kalshi\\\" \u2192 deep link into Kalshi app/web\",\" \",\"-### Offline Handling\",\"-\",\"-If the app is offline when a push arrives:\",\"-- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \\\"signal-{marketId}\\\"` \u2014 stale signals are replaced, not stacked.\",\"-- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \\\"signal-{marketId}\\\"`.\",\"-\",\"-Set `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) \u2014 signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.\",\"-\",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer\",\"+## 9. Notification Permission Strategy (iOS)\",\" \",\"-Per team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:\",\"+**Do NOT request permission on first launch.** Earn it first.\",\" \",\"-- Mobile: Add subtitle \\\"Paper Trade \u00b7 Not a live order\\\" when `executed: false`\",\"-- Slack: Append \\\"Paper trading mode\\\" in context block\",\"+1. Show value: display 2\u20133 signal alerts as in-app banners (no system prompt yet)\",\"+2. At third in-app signal, show a custom pre-permission screen: \\\"Get alerts when high-confidence signals appear \u2014 even when the app is closed\\\"\",\"+3. Only then call `requestAuthorization(options: [.alert, .sound, .badge])`\",\"+4. If denied: fall back to in-app banners + Slack only; re-ask after 30 days if user views signals 3+ times\",\" \",\"+**Android:** Request `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission (Android 13+) using the same two-step pattern.\",\"+\",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia\",\"+## 10. Notes for API Owners (Bob / Mia)\",\" \",\"-1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.\",\"-2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.\",\"-3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.\",\"+- The existing `GET /api/signals` payload contains everything needed (ticker, confidence, edge, reason, contracts, risk). No new endpoint required for v1.\",\"+- Future: consider `GET /api/signals/stream` (SSE) to eliminate the 60s polling lag.\",\"+- Auth: the notification registration endpoint must require `Authorization: Bearer` header (per consensus.md rule #3).\",\" \",\" ---\",\" \",\"-## 10. Acceptance Criteria\",\"+## 11. Open Questions / Future Work\",\" \",\"-- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`\",\"-- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes\",\"-- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced\",\"-- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec\",\"-- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel\",\"-- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack\",\"-- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`\",\"-- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device\",\"+| Item | Owner | Priority |\",\"+|------|-------|----------|\",\"+| APNs certificate provisioning | Judy + Eve | High |\",\"+| FCM project credentials | Judy + Eve | High |\",\"+| Slack webhook URL for prod | Alice/CEO | High |\",\"+| Push permission opt-in analytics | Judy + Grace | Medium |\",\"+| Exit signal notifications (`signalType=\\\"exit\\\"`) | Judy | Low |\",\"+| SSE streaming endpoint | Bob/Mia | Low |\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Push Notification Spec \u2014 Trade Signal Alerts\\n\\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n**Task:** T268\\n**Status:** Final\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Overview\\n\\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. Notifications fire when the trading pipeline generates high-confidence signals (\u226580% confidence, per team consensus). Users are alerted on mobile (iOS/Android) and optionally via Slack webhook.\\n\\nSignal source: `GET http://localhost:3200/api/signals`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\\n\\nA notification is triggered when **all** of the following are true:\\n\\n| Condition | Rule |\\n|-----------|------|\\n| Signal confidence | `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) |\\n| Signal type | `signalType == \\\"entry\\\"` (not exit or hold) |\\n| Market not already notified | No notification sent for same `marketId` + `side` in the last **15 minutes** |\\n| Frequency limit not exceeded | Global cap: max **5 notifications per hour** across all markets |\\n| Trading not in cooldown | Respect per-market cooldown window (see \u00a75) |\\n\\n**Example triggering signal** (from live API):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n  \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n  \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n  \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n  \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n  \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n  \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n  \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n  \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\\n\\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"notification\\\": {\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n    \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES \u00b7 95% confidence \u00b7 Edge: +23\u00a2 \u00b7 29 contracts recommended\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"trade_signal\\\",\\n    \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\\n    \\\"marketId\\\": \\\"m4\\\",\\n    \\\"ticker\\\": \\\"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n    \\\"marketTitle\\\": \\\"Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\\",\\n    \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"mean_reversion\\\",\\n    \\\"side\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n    \\\"signalType\\\": \\\"entry\\\",\\n    \\\"confidence\\\": 0.95,\\n    \\\"expectedEdge\\\": 23,\\n    \\\"currentPrice\\\": 64,\\n    \\\"targetPrice\\\": 64,\\n    \\\"recommendedContracts\\\": 29,\\n    \\\"riskAmount\\\": 1856,\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\\\",\\n    \\\"generatedAt\\\": \\\"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\\\",\\n    \\\"deepLink\\\": \\\"agentplanet://signals/m4\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"apns\\\": {\\n    \\\"headers\\\": {\\n      \\\"apns-priority\\\": \\\"10\\\",\\n      \\\"apns-push-type\\\": \\\"alert\\\",\\n      \\\"apns-expiration\\\": \\\"300\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"payload\\\": {\\n      \\\"aps\\\": {\\n        \\\"alert\\\": {\\n          \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\",\\n          \\\"body\\\": \\\"BUY YES \u00b7 95% confidence \u00b7 Edge: +23\u00a2 \u00b7 29 contracts recommended\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"sound\\\": \\\"default\\\",\\n        \\\"badge\\\": 1,\\n        \\\"thread-id\\\": \\\"trade_signals\\\",\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\",\\n        \\\"mutable-content\\\": 1\\n      }\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"android\\\": {\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"HIGH\\\",\\n    \\\"ttl\\\": \\\"300s\\\",\\n    \\\"notification\\\": {\\n      \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"trade_signals_high\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"ic_signal_alert\\\",\\n      \\\"color\\\": \\\"#00C853\\\",\\n      \\\"click_action\\\": \\\"OPEN_SIGNAL_DETAIL\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"\ud83d\udfe2 *Trade Signal Alert*\\\",\\n  \\\"blocks\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"header\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"plain_text\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"\ud83d\udcc8 Trade Signal \u2014 BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\\\"\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"section\\\",\\n      \\\"fields\\\": [\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Strategy:*\\\\nmean_reversion\\\" },\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Side:*\\\\nBUY YES\\\" },\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Confidence:*\\\\n95%\\\" },\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Expected Edge:*\\\\n+23\u00a2 per contract\\\" },\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Recommended:*\\\\n29 contracts\\\" },\\n        { \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Risk Amount:*\\\\n$18.56\\\" }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"section\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\\\n*Current Price:* 64\u00a2 YES\\\"\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"context\\\",\\n      \\\"elements\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"mrkdwn\\\",\\n          \\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z \u00b7 Paper trading mode\\\"\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Delivery Channels\\n\\n### 4.1 Mobile Push\\n\\n| Platform | Service | Notes |\\n|----------|---------|-------|\\n| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \\\"trade_signals\\\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |\\n| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \\\"trade_signals_high\\\"` \u2014 users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |\\n\\n**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \\\"TRADE_SIGNAL\\\"`):\\n- **View Signal** \u2014 opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)\\n- **Dismiss** \u2014 no action\\n\\n**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`\\n- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)\\n- Sound: enabled by default\\n- Vibration: enabled\\n\\n### 4.2 Slack Webhook\\n\\n- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`\\n- POST to webhook URL when signal fires\\n- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved\\n- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery\\n\\n### 4.3 Delivery Priority\\n\\n1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)\\n2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\\n\\nThese limits prevent alert fatigue:\\n\\n| Scope | Limit | Window |\\n|-------|-------|--------|\\n| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |\\n| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |\\n| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00\u201307:00 local time (configurable) |\\n| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |\\n\\n**Cooldown logic:**\\n```\\nnotificationKey = \\\"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\\\"\\nif lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:\\n    skip \u2014 cooldown active\\nelse:\\n    fire notification\\n    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now\\n```\\n\\n**Hourly cap:**\\n```\\nhourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes\\nif hourlyCount >= 5:\\n    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)\\n    log: \\\"Hourly cap reached \u2014 notification queued\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow\\n\\n```\\n[Signal Generator - port 3200]\\n        \u2502\\n        \u25bc\\n[GET /api/signals every 30s]\\n        \u2502\\n        \u25bc\\n[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] \u2500\u2500No\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Drop\\n        \u2502 Yes\\n        \u25bc\\n[Filter: signalType == \\\"entry\\\"?] \u2500\u2500No\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Drop\\n        \u2502 Yes\\n        \u25bc\\n[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] \u2500\u2500Yes\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Skip\\n        \u2502 No\\n        \u25bc\\n[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] \u2500\u2500Yes\u2500\u2500\u25b6 Queue\\n        \u2502 No\\n        \u25bc\\n[Build notification payload (\u00a73)]\\n        \u2502\\n        \u251c\u2500\u2500\u25b6 [Send APNs / FCM]\\n        \u2502\\n        \u2514\u2500\u2500\u25b6 [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)\\n        \u2502\\n        \u25bc\\n[Update lastNotified[key] = now]\\n[Increment hourly counter]\\n[Log delivery result]\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. Implementation Notes\\n\\n### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)\\n\\n```javascript\\n// Key environment variables\\nAPNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID\\nAPNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID\\nAPNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file\\nAPNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app\\nFCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key\\nSLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...\\n\\n// Polling interval\\nconst SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds\\n\\n// Thresholds\\nconst MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;\\nconst COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes\\nconst HOURLY_CAP = 5;\\nconst BURST_CAP = 3;\\nconst BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\\n```\\n\\n### Deep Linking\\n\\nApp must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.\\n\\n### Offline Handling\\n\\nIf the app is offline when a push arrives:\\n- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \\\"signal-{marketId}\\\"` \u2014 stale signals are replaced, not stacked.\\n- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \\\"signal-{marketId}\\\"`.\\n\\nSet `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) \u2014 signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer\\n\\nPer team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:\\n\\n- Mobile: Add subtitle \\\"Paper Trade \u00b7 Not a live order\\\" when `executed: false`\\n- Slack: Append \\\"Paper trading mode\\\" in context block\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia\\n\\n1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.\\n2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.\\n3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria\\n\\n- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`\\n- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes\\n- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced\\n- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec\\n- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel\\n- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack\\n- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`\\n- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device\\n\"}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:52:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_011wuXGAoxVY554fEE2goMWB\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now mark the task done and update status.md.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3506,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":31166,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens