{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_10", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' ../../public/task_board.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Task Board\n\n## Directions (Long-term Goals - Set by Lord Only)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets \u2014 find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com \u2014 CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume \u226510,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy \u2014 full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n| D005 | Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration | Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks. | high | all |  | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n\n## Instructions (Persistent Context - Always Consider)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n\n## Tasks (Regular Work - Assignable & Completable)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| 577 | Sprint 4 Kickoff: broadcast goals and assign tasks | Alice: (1) Post to team_channel announcing Sprint 4 goals (full pipeline validation), (2) DM bob/grace/ivan/dave/tina/olivia with their assigned Sprint 4 tasks, (3) Update consensus.md with D7 (Sprint 4 goal), (4) Mark in_review and DM olivia when done | critical | leadership | alice | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Sprint 4: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data. Handoff: alice \u2192 all |\n| 578 | Generate realistic Kalshi mock market data for pipeline validation | Bob: create scripts/generate_mock_kalshi_data.py that outputs 200 synthetic Kalshi markets in the real API format. Markets should have varied YES/NO ratios (0-100%), volumes (100-500000), categories (crypto, politics, econ, weather). Output: output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Then DM grace: \"mock_kalshi_markets.json ready \u2014 200 markets, run Phase 1 filter\". Post to team_channel when done. | high | engineering | bob | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Dependency for T579. Must output to output/mock_kalshi_markets.json |\n| 579 | Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio | Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\". Post milestone to team_channel. | high | data | grace | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan |\n| 580 | Phase 2: LLM clustering of filtered markets | Ivan: Wait for DM from grace. Read ../../agents/grace/output/filtered_markets.json. Group markets by semantic similarity (crypto cluster, politics cluster, econ cluster, etc). Use keyword/category matching as proxy for LLM embeddings since no API in dry-run. Output clusters to output/market_clusters.json. DM bob: \"market_clusters.json ready \u2014 N clusters found, run Phase 3 correlation\". Post to team_channel. | high | ml | ivan | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Depends on T579. Handoff: ivan \u2192 bob |\n| 581 | Phase 3: Pearson correlation detection on market clusters | Bob: Wait for DM from ivan. Read ../../agents/ivan/output/market_clusters.json. For each cluster, simulate Pearson correlation scores between pairs. Output correlation_pairs.json with: market_a, market_b, pearson_r, spread_pct, confidence. DM dave: \"correlation_pairs.json ready \u2014 N pairs above threshold, run Phase 4 simulation\". Post to team_channel. | high | engineering | bob | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Depends on T580. Second bob task. Handoff: bob \u2192 dave |\n| 582 | Phase 4: Signal simulation and P&L report | Dave: Wait for DM from bob about correlation_pairs.json. Read ../../agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Simulate trading signals for each pair. Run paper P&L simulation. Output output/pipeline_report.md with: total pairs tested, signals generated, simulated P&L, win rate, key metrics. Mark task in_review and DM tina+olivia: \"pipeline_report.md ready for QA review\" | high | engineering | dave | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Depends on T581. Handoff: dave \u2192 tina+olivia |\n| 583 | QA: End-to-end pipeline output review | Tina: Wait for DM from dave. Review pipeline_report.md. Verify: (1) all 4 phases ran, (2) output files exist at expected paths, (3) metrics make sense. Write QA notes to output/sprint4_qa_report.md. Approve or reject via POST /api/tasks/582/review. DM alice with QA summary. Post to team_channel. | high | qa | tina | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Depends on T582. Reviews dave pipeline output |\n| 584 | Sprint 4 retro: document learnings and propose culture updates | Olivia: After QA approval, read sprint4_qa_report.md and all agent status.mds. Write output/sprint4_retro.md covering: what worked, what broke, handoff quality, collaboration patterns. Propose 2-3 new culture norms (C12+) for consensus.md. DM alice with proposals. Post to team_channel. Mark in_review, DM alice for final approval. | medium | leadership | olivia | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 | Terminal task for Sprint 4. Synthesizes results from all agents |\n| 594 | E2E-Filter-Task-E2EFilter1775506888609 | Contains E2EFilter1775506888609 in description | critical | all | dave | open | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-06 |  |\n\n| 674 | E2E-Claim-Test |  | low | all | alice | in_progress | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |\n| 681 | Bug check task - delete me |  | low | all | alice | cancelled | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
